title: Group Road Ride - Metcalf
description:
Start with Kennedy, then into the Leyland Park maze, then a stop at the park on Mockingbird Hill Lane (water and bathrooms, mile 12).  Over IBM and onto San Felipe Rd and the gentle climb to Metcalf Moto Park (water and bathrooms, mile 32).  Dropping down the steep side of Metcalf take an immediate left to Bailey and then right onto McKean and back to Mikes Bikes.  Route is 56 miles with 4,800 feet of climbing. 

Important!! Non-members be sure to sign the waiver on the Los Gatos Bicycle Racing Club website.

meet_up_location: Mike's Bikes, 201 N Santa Cruz Ave, Los Gatos, California 95030, United States
title: Sunday Road Ride: Counter-clockwise IBM
description:
Hello team,
Note, there is anticipated rain for this Sunday, if it's raining on Sunday morning, or if there is a high chance of rain for Sunday morning on Saturday, this ride will be canceled. 
This Sunday, we will head to IBM from the counter clockwise direction, ascending from the north entrance. Before beginning the ascent up, we will stop for bathroom and water refill at the Almaden Quicksilver Park Mockingbird Hill Entrance. Upon completing the climb, we will do a celebratory lap around the IBM campus before beginning the descent down the north entrance (same side we came up) and heading back to Mike’s Bike’s in Los Gatos. The route is 30 miles with 2,200 ft of elevation gain. We will meet at Mike’s Bike’s in Los Gatos at 8:30 am and wheels will roll at 8:35 am sharp. This is a no-drop ride. I will do my best to keep the group together.

有两个大爬坡，分别是大家熟悉的 Old La Honda，和很多人熟悉的从Bike Hut开始的Tunitas Creek Rd

预计总时间6 hours

本路线也叫避暑路线，因为在树林中穿行，或是海边吹风。起始从Redwood Townhall出发，这也是在 [旧金山湾区骑行路线 第一章 练](https://rangerway.com/way/cycling-routes-at-bay-area) 介绍过的OLH老本田训练路线的起始点，可以把这个地方看作是湾区骑行的一个hub，因为很多骑行路线无论是转山还是休闲骑还是辣堡团，都会以这里为起点或者经过这里。
这一路上有很多可以驻足休息的好玩的地方，像Pescadero小镇和San Gregorio小店，还有下图的 The Bike Hut。一路的风景也有很多令我初见惊艳的地方。期待您也去探索一番，发现不一样的景色。

title: AV-A Ride Saturday 9/13/25:  Cloverdale to AV Picnic!
description: Join us for another Saturday A ride. It looks like another perfect day to play bikes so let’s go to the coast and do a Cloverdale loop. I designed the route to finish on Kings Mountain where we can meet at Huddart Park for the Alto Velo Picnic which starts @ 3pm.
meet_up_location: Summit Bikes Palo Alto

title: Saturday A Ride: 8am choose your own adventure
description: It’s been a looooong time since the Saturday ride went up Bohlman. We will start by going down foothill and through Stevens Creek Reservoir, stopping for water/bathrooms just before hopping over Mt. Eden and going down into Saratoga.
meet_up_location: Summit Bikes Palo Alto

title: Saturday A Ride- Big Basin + Shake Shack
description: Saturday looks like better weather than the last big basin ride- so we’ll try take two on this. We’ll regroup at the top of page mill and bear creek, and probably take a quick stop in Boulder Creek.
meet_up_location: Summit Bikes Palo Alto

title: Saturday A Ride 8/23 - Native Sons and Purisima Creek
description: Exploring roads like Star Hill Rd and Native Sons Rd, with a climb up Kings Mountain and a descent down Tunitas to Half Moon Bay for coffee and snacks.
meet_up_location: Summit Bicycles, Palo Alto
